Package ohos.distributedhardware.devicemanager

Interface ReturnCode


  • public interface ReturnCode
    Defines the return codes for operations related to device management.
    Since:
    4
    See Also:
    DeviceManager

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field Description
      static int ERR_ABANDON_BY_NEW_REQUEST
      Indicates that the existing request is aborted due to a new request.
      static int ERR_ADD_MEMBER_FAIL
      Indicates that an error occurs when the application sends a request to join a group.
      static int ERR_CALLBACK_ALREADY_EXIST
      Indicates that the callback to be registered for listening for device state changes has been registered.
      static int ERR_CALLBACK_OUT_OF_LIMIT
      Indicates that the number of registered callbacks used for listening for device state changes exceeds the upper limit.
      static int ERR_CHANNEL_BROKEN
      Indicates that the cross-device channel is broken ungracefully.

      Indicates that the discovery service fails to be connected.

      Indicates that the group fails to be created.

      Indicates that the discovery service is disconnected.
      static int ERR_DM_SERVICE_DISCONNECTED
      Indicates that the device management service is not connected.
      static int ERR_GET_LOCAL_DEVICE_INFO_FAIL
      Indicates that the local device information fails to be obtained.
      static int ERR_JOIN_GROUP_FAIL
      Indicates that the application fails to join the group.

      Indicates that the application being called is not in the foreground.

      Indicates that the running application is not in the foreground.

      Indicates that the cross-device channel fails to be opened.

      Indicates that the input parameters are invalid.

      Indicates that the callback to be registered for listening for device state changes has been destroyed.

      Indicates that the request is cancelled.
      static int ERR_REQUEST_QR_FAIL
      Indicates that the QR code fails to be generated.
      static int ERR_SESSION_NOT_EXIST
      Indicates that the session information does not exist.
      static int ERR_SET_FRIEND_LIST_FAIL
      Indicates that the allow list for group access fails to be set.
      static int ERR_START_REMOTE_DM
      Indicates that the remote device management service fails to be started.
      static int ERR_TIMEOUT
      Indicates that the request times out.
      static int ERR_UNREGISTER_CALLBACK_NOT_EXIST
      Indicates that the callback to be unregistered does not exist.
      static int ERR_USER_BUSY
      Indicates that the remote device is busy and the request is rejected.
      static int ERR_USER_REJECT
      Indicates that the request is rejected by the remote user.
      static int ERR_WRITE_EXT_INFO_FAIL
      Indicates that the group information fails to be written.
      static int STOP_MIGRATE_ACTION
      Indicates that the current task migration is cancelled.
      static int SUCCESS
      Indicates that the method call is successful.
